# Copy to .env and fill in ONE of the two credentials. That is the only required part. Never commit
# the result: .litter-box/.gitignore already excludes it.
#
# A subscription OAuth token, from `claude setup-token`. Bills the subscription.
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=
# Or a dedicated, spend-capped console API key. Set one or the other, never both: passing both
# lets a stale key shadow a valid token inside claude, which is a 401 that looks like an outage.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Every other variable the loop reads also works here, so this file can hold a whole permanent local
# configuration instead of a shell full of exports. Precedence: an exported variable with a non-empty
# value beats this file, and this file beats .litter-box/config.conf.
#
# Syntax is KEY=value, one per line. Blank lines and `#` comment lines are skipped, a leading
# `export ` is allowed, and one matched pair of surrounding quotes is stripped. Nothing else is
# interpreted: no escape sequences, and no trailing `#` comment, since a credential may legally
# contain one.
#
# MAX_ITERS=1
# DRY_RUN=0
# REPAIR_BUDGET=2
# NTFY_TOPIC=
#
# GATE_CMD set HERE only replaces the gate command. Unlike an exported GATE_CMD it never switches the
# Docker preflight off, because a permanent untracked file must not silently disable the sandbox for
# every future run.
# GATE_CMD=
#
# IMPL_CMD, FIX_CMD, REVIEW_CMD, NOTIFY_CMD, CI_WAIT_CMD, CI_APPEAR_CMD and MERGE_CMD each replace
# one subprocess, so the loop can be driven without Docker or GitHub.
# IMPL_CMD=
